<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 6:24PM EDT  by NWS Wakefield</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL AFFECT FLUVANNA COUNTY...
At 624 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Palmyra, moving
southeast at 20 mph.
Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail are possible with this
storm.
Locations impacted include...
Palmyra, Fork Union, Columbia, Scottsville, Dixie, Nahor, Stage
Junction, Shores, Central Plains, Bremo Bluff, Antioch, Cohasset,
Hardware, Carysbrook, Wilmington and Cunningham.
If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</description>
